# Drakemont System Maintenance Checklist

**Client Name:** _______________________  
**System Serviced:** ___________________  
**Date of Service:** ____________________

## Step 1: Initial System Inspection

- [ ] Inspect physical components for wear and tear  
- [ ] Check fluid levels and replace as necessary  
- [ ] Inspect electrical connections for corrosion or damage  
- [ ] Verify safety systems (e.g., pressure relief valves, emergency shutoffs)

## Step 2: System Performance Review

- [ ] Test all major system components (PLC, sensors, actuators)  
- [ ] Check for any error codes or system alarms  
- [ ] Monitor system performance metrics (e.g., power consumption, efficiency)  
- [ ] Verify system communication between integrated components

## Step 3: Troubleshooting (if applicable)

- [ ] Identify any system issues or faults  
- [ ] Resolve identified problems (e.g., replace faulty sensors or reprogram PLCs)  
- [ ] Perform test runs to confirm system stability

## Step 4: Preventative Maintenance Tasks

- [ ] Clean and lubricate moving parts  
- [ ] Replace any worn-out components (e.g., seals, filters)  
- [ ] Test backup systems (e.g., UPS, emergency power)  
- [ ] Update software/firmware if applicable

## Step 5: Documentation and Client Report

- [ ] Provide client with a maintenance report detailing all actions taken  
- [ ] Suggest any upgrades or improvements (e.g., new technologies or optimization)  
- [ ] Set a schedule for next maintenance check
